372edee2-c6d3-4c01-87cd-2f5b692ad8d3.content:
GLOBAL TECH SOLUTIONS INC., a Delaware corporation (“Employer”), and
Priya Patel, an individual resident of 789 Market Street, San Francisco, CA 94103 (“Employee”).
RECITALS
WHEREAS, Employer desires to employ Employee, and Employee desires to accept such employment under the terms below;
1. Position and Duties
1.1 Employer hereby employs Employee as Senior Software Engineer. Employee shall perform duties as reasonably assigned by Employer’s CTO.
1.2 Employee shall devote full business time and best efforts to the performance of duties.
2. Term of Employment
2.1 Employment shall commence on October 15, 2025 and continue at will until terminated by either party pursuant to Article 7.
3. Compensation and Benefits
3.1 Salary: $150,000 per annum, paid bi-weekly.
3.2 Bonus: Eligible for annual performance bonus up to 15% of base salary.
3.3 Benefits: Health, dental, vision coverage; 401(k) matching; four weeks’ paid vacation.
4. Confidentiality and Invention Assignment
4.1 Employee shall sign the Confidentiality & Invention Assignment Agreement attached as Exhibit A.
4.2 All inventions created during employment belong exclusively to Employer.
5. Non-Compete and Non-Solicitation
5.1 During employment and for six (6) months thereafter, Employee shall not compete with Employer within the United States.
5.2 Employee shall not solicit Employer’s employees or clients for twelve (12) months post-termination.
6. Termination
6.1 Employer may terminate for Cause (as defined below) immediately; for convenience upon thirty (30) days’ notice.
6.2 “Cause” includes: (a) material breach, (b) dishonesty, (c) gross misconduct.
7. Governing Law
7.1 This Agreement shall be governed by the laws of the State of California.
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have executed this Agreement as of the date first written above.

cad4b24d-34b3-4554-8dd0-9e06ebfbe045.content:
between:
Sunrise Properties LLC, a California limited liability company (“Landlord”), and
GreenLeaf Café, Inc., a California corporation (“Tenant”).
1. Demised Premises
1.1 Landlord leases to Tenant the premises located at 101 Main Street, Suite 200, Palo Alto, CA, approximately 2,500 square feet (the “Premises”).
2. Lease Term
2.1 Term: December 1, 2025 through November 30, 2028, with one five-year renewal option.
3. Rent and Additional Charges
3.1 Base Rent: $10,000 per month, payable on the first day of each month.
3.2 Operating Expenses: Tenant shall pay Tenant’s Pro Rata Share (30%) of all Common Area Maintenance, property taxes, and insurance.
4. Use of Premises
4.1 Permitted Use: Operation of a café and related retail business.
4.2 Tenant shall comply with all laws, maintain premises in good order, and make no structural alterations without Landlord’s prior written consent.
5. Security Deposit
5.1 Tenant shall deposit $20,000 upon execution, refundable at lease end, less any deductions for damage or unpaid charges.
6. Insurance and Indemnity
6.1 Tenant shall maintain commercial general liability insurance with minimum limits of $1,000,000 per occurrence.
6.2 Tenant shall indemnify Landlord against all claims arising from Tenant’s use of the Premises.
7. Default and Remedies
7.1 Events of Default: Non-payment of rent, breach of covenants, abandonment.
7.2 Remedies: Landlord may terminate lease or pursue any remedy available at law or equity after ten (10) days’ written notice.
8. Governing Law
8.1 California law governs this Lease.
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties execute this Lease as of the date first above written.

139ea2c1-070f-47fb-9094-beec20e63f3b.content:
between:
ABC TECHNOLOGIES, INC., a Delaware corporation with its principal place of business at 123 Innovation Drive, Wilmington, DE 19801 (“Disclosing Party”),
and
XYZ SOLUTIONS LLC, a California limited liability company with its principal place of business at 456 Enterprise Avenue, San Francisco, CA 94105 (“Receiving Party”).
RECITALS
WHEREAS, Disclosing Party possesses certain confidential and proprietary information; and
WHEREAS, Receiving Party desires to receive such information for the sole purpose of evaluating a potential business relationship (the “Purpose”);
NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual promises and covenants herein, the parties agree as follows:
1. Definitions
1.1 “Confidential Information” means any technical, financial, business, or other information disclosed by Disclosing Party, whether in written, oral, electronic, or other form, including but not limited to:
(a) Business plans, forecasts, and strategies;
(b) Product designs, formulas, and specifications;
(c) Software code, algorithms, and documentation;
(d) Customer lists, pricing, and marketing data.
1.2 Confidential Information does not include information that:
(a) Is or becomes publicly known through no breach of this Agreement;
(b) Is received from a third party without breach of any obligation;
(c) Was independently developed by Receiving Party without use of Disclosing Party’s Confidential Information.
2. Obligations of Receiving Party
2.1 Receiving Party shall hold all Confidential Information in strict confidence and shall not disclose it to any third party without Disclosing Party’s prior written consent.
2.2 Receiving Party shall use Confidential Information solely for the Purpose and shall limit access to those employees or contractors who need to know, provided such persons are bound by confidentiality obligations no less stringent than those in this Agreement.
2.3 Receiving Party shall use at least the same degree of care to protect Confidential Information as it uses to protect its own confidential information, but in no event less than reasonable care.
3. Term and Termination
3.1 This Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and continue for a period of three (3) years, unless earlier terminated by either party upon thirty (30) days’ prior written notice.
3.2 Upon termination or expiration, Receiving Party shall promptly return or destroy all Confidential Information and certify in writing that no copies have been retained.
4. No License
Nothing in this Agreement grants Receiving Party any license or other rights to the Confidential Information except as expressly set forth herein.
5. Remedies
Receiving Party acknowledges that any unauthorized use or disclosure of Confidential Information may cause irreparable harm to Disclosing Party for which monetary damages may be inadequate. Disclosing Party shall therefore be entitled to injunctive relief in addition to any other remedies available at law or in equity.
6. Governing Law and Venue
This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of Delaware, without regard to its conflict of law principles. Any dispute shall be brought exclusively in the state or federal courts located in New Castle County, Delaware.
7. Entire Agreement
This Agreement constitutes the entire understanding between the parties with respect to the subject matter and supersedes all prior discussions and agreements, whether written or oral.
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties hereto have executed this Agreement as of the Effective Date.
                                   **ABC TECHNOLOGIES, INC.**  
           ________________________________  
           Name: Jane Doe  
           Title: Chief Executive Officer  

                                   **XYZ SOLUTIONS LLC**  
           ________________________________  
           Name: John Smith  
           Title: Managing Partner

61589d50-5bc5-43e1-9201-eb2ecbb02f16.content:
between:
Industrial Solutions Co., an Ohio corporation (“Seller”), and
Metro Builders Group, an Ohio limited liability company (“Buyer”).
Section 1 – Goods Sold
1.1 Seller agrees to sell, and Buyer agrees to purchase, the goods listed in Exhibit A attached hereto, including specifications, quantities, and delivery schedules.
Section 2 – Price and Payment
2.1 Total Purchase Price: $120,000.
2.2 Payment Terms: 40% deposit upon order, balance due net 30 days after delivery.
Section 3 – Delivery and Risk of Loss
3.1 Delivery Terms: FOB Seller’s warehouse, Columbus, OH.
3.2 Risk of Loss passes to Buyer upon loading onto carrier.
Section 4 – Inspection and Acceptance
4.1 Buyer shall inspect goods within seven (7) days of delivery and notify Seller of any non-conformity.
4.2 Failure to notify constitutes acceptance.
Section 5 – Warranties
5.1 Seller warrants goods shall conform to specifications and be free of defects for ninety (90) days from delivery.
5.2 Exclusive remedy for breach of warranty is repair or replacement at Seller’s option.
Section 6 – Limitation of Liability
6.1 Seller’s liability shall not exceed the purchase price of the non-conforming goods; no liability for indirect or consequential damages.
Section 7 – Governing Law
7.1 This Contract shall be governed by and construed under the laws of the State of Ohio.
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties hereto have executed this Contract as of the date first above written.

     ________________________________  
     Name: Mark Stevens  
     Title: Vice President  

             **METRO BUILDERS GROUP**  
     ________________________________  
     Name: Laura Thompson  
     Title: COO

MASTER SERVICES AGREEMENT
(High-Risk Commercial Template for Testing Purposes Only)
This Master Services Agreement (“Agreement”) is entered into as of [Effective Date], by and between:
[Company Name], a [State/Country] corporation with its principal place of business at [Address] (“Company”),
and
[Client Name], a [State/Country] entity with its principal place of business at [Address] (“Client”).
Company and Client may be referred to individually as a “Party” and collectively as the “Parties.”

1. SCOPE OF SERVICES
1.1 Company shall provide the services described in one or more Statements of Work (“SOW”).
1.2 Company retains sole discretion over methods, tools, personnel, and technologies used to perform the Services.
1.3 No exclusivity is granted unless explicitly stated in a signed SOW.

2. PAYMENT TERMS
2.1 Client shall pay all fees within seven (7) days of invoice date.
2.2 Late payments shall accrue interest at the greater of 2.5% per month or the maximum permitted by law, compounded monthly.
2.3 Client shall reimburse all collection costs, including attorneys’ fees.

3. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY
3.1 Assignment. Client hereby irrevocably assigns to Company all right, title, and interest in any feedback, suggestions, derivative works, or modifications related to Company’s technology.
3.2 Work Product Ownership. Unless otherwise specified in a signed SOW, all deliverables, source code, inventions, processes, trade secrets, and documentation created under this Agreement shall remain the exclusive property of Company.
3.3 Moral Rights Waiver. Client waives any moral rights or similar rights to the fullest extent permitted by law.

4. CONFIDENTIALITY
4.1 “Confidential Information” includes all technical, financial, strategic, and operational information disclosed by either Party.
4.2 The receiving Party shall:
Protect Confidential Information with at least the same degree of care it uses for its own.
Not disclose such information to any third party without prior written consent.
4.3 These obligations survive termination for ten (10) years, or perpetually for trade secrets.

5. DATA PROTECTION AND SECURITY
5.1 Client acknowledges that Services may involve processing of personal data.
5.2 Company makes no warranty that its systems are immune from cyberattack, intrusion, or data breach.
5.3 Client assumes all regulatory risk associated with data processed under this Agreement, including fines, penalties, and notification obligations.
5.4 Client shall indemnify Company against any claims arising from data provided by Client.

6. WARRANTIES DISCLAIMER
6.1 SERVICES ARE PROVIDED “AS IS” AND “AS AVAILABLE.”
6.2 COMPANY DISCLAIMS ALL WARRANTIES, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING:
MERCHANTABILITY
FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE
NON-INFRINGEMENT
UNINTERRUPTED OR ERROR-FREE OPERATION
6.3 Company does not guarantee regulatory compliance of deliverables.

7. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY
7.1 To the maximum extent permitted by law, Company’s total aggregate liability shall not exceed the total fees paid by Client in the thirty (30) days preceding the claim.
7.2 Under no circumstances shall Company be liable for:
Indirect damages
Consequential damages
Lost profits
Business interruption
Loss of data
7.3 These limitations apply even if a remedy fails of its essential purpose.

8. INDEMNIFICATION (HIGH-RISK ALLOCATION)
8.1 Client shall defend, indemnify, and hold harmless Company and its affiliates, officers, directors, employees, and agents from and against any and all claims, including third-party claims, regulatory penalties, and governmental investigations arising from:
Client’s use of the Services
Client’s data
Client’s violation of law
Any integration with third-party systems
8.2 This indemnification obligation is uncapped and survives termination.

9. LIQUIDATED DAMAGES
9.1 If Client breaches Sections 3 (IP), 4 (Confidentiality), or 8 (Indemnification), Client agrees to pay liquidated damages of $250,000 per breach, acknowledging that actual damages would be difficult to calculate.
9.2 Liquidated damages are cumulative and not exclusive of other remedies.

10. TERMINATION
10.1 Company may terminate this Agreement immediately for convenience upon written notice.
10.2 Client may terminate only upon:
90 days’ written notice; and
Payment of all remaining fees due under any active SOW.
10.3 Upon termination:
All licenses immediately cease.
Client shall delete all Company proprietary materials.
Outstanding payment obligations accelerate and become immediately due.

11. NON-COMPETE AND NON-SOLICITATION
11.1 During the term and for two (2) years thereafter, Client shall not develop, market, or support any product substantially similar to Company’s offerings.
11.2 Client shall not solicit or hire Company employees during the term and for 24 months thereafter.

12. DISPUTE RESOLUTION
12.1 Any dispute shall be resolved exclusively by binding arbitration under the rules of [Arbitration Body].
12.2 Arbitration shall occur in [Jurisdiction].
12.3 Each Party waives:
Jury trial rights
Class action participation
Consolidated proceedings

के बीच संपादित किया गया।

1. नियुक्ति (Appointment)
नियोक्ता कर्मचारी को सॉफ्टवेयर इंजीनियर के पद पर नियुक्त करता है। कर्मचारी इस पद से संबंधित सभी कर्तव्यों का ईमानदारी एवं निष्ठा से पालन करेगा।

2. कार्य अवधि (Tenure)
यह अनुबंध 01 जनवरी 2026 से प्रारंभ होकर अनिश्चित काल तक प्रभावी रहेगा, जब तक कि इसे इस अनुबंध के प्रावधानों के अनुसार समाप्त न किया जाए।

3. कार्य स्थल (Place of Work)
कर्मचारी का कार्य स्थल नियोक्ता का कार्यालय या कोई अन्य स्थान हो सकता है, जैसा कि नियोक्ता समय-समय पर निर्धारित करे।

4. वेतन एवं लाभ (Compensation & Benefits)
कर्मचारी को ₹10,00,000 (दस लाख रुपये) वार्षिक वेतन दिया जाएगा। इसके अतिरिक्त, कंपनी की नीति के अनुसार बोनस, बीमा एवं अन्य लाभ भी प्रदान किए जा सकते हैं।

5. गोपनीयता (Confidentiality)
कर्मचारी कंपनी की सभी गोपनीय सूचनाओं, तकनीकी जानकारी, व्यापार रहस्यों एवं ग्राहक विवरण को गोपनीय रखेगा। यह दायित्व सेवा समाप्ति के पश्चात भी लागू रहेगा।

6. बौद्धिक संपदा अधिकार (Intellectual Property Rights)
कर्मचारी द्वारा सेवा अवधि के दौरान विकसित की गई सभी खोजें, सॉफ़्टवेयर, दस्तावेज़ एवं सामग्री नियोक्ता की बौद्धिक संपत्ति मानी जाएगी।

7. सेवा समाप्ति (Termination)
किसी भी पक्ष द्वारा 30 दिन का लिखित नोटिस देकर इस अनुबंध को समाप्त किया जा सकता है। गंभीर अनुशासनहीनता की स्थिति में नियोक्ता बिना नोटिस सेवा समाप्त कर सकता है।

8. गैर-प्रतिस्पर्धा (Non-Compete Clause)
सेवा समाप्ति के पश्चात कर्मचारी 6 माह तक किसी प्रतिस्पर्धी संस्था में कार्य नहीं करेगा।

9. विवाद निपटान (Dispute Resolution)
इस अनुबंध से उत्पन्न किसी भी विवाद का निपटान भारतीय मध्यस्थता एवं सुलह अधिनियम, 1996 के अंतर्गत किया जाएगा।

10. लागू कानून (Governing Law)
यह अनुबंध भारत के कानूनों द्वारा शासित एवं नियंत्रित होगा।

and

1.2 Company retains sole discretion over methods, tools, personnel, and technologies used to perform the Services.
1.3 No exclusivity is granted unless explicitly stated in a signed SOW.

2.1 Client shall pay all fees within seven (7) days of invoice date.
2.2 Late payments shall accrue interest at the greater of 2.5% per month or the maximum permitted by law, compounded monthly.

3.1 Assignment. Client hereby irrevocably assigns to Company all right, title, and interest in any feedback, suggestions, derivative works, or modifications related to Company’s technology.

3.3 Moral Rights Waiver. Client waives any moral rights or similar rights to the fullest extent permitted by law.

4. CONFIDENTIALITY
4.1 “Confidential Information” includes all technical, financial, strategic, and operational information disclosed by either Party.
4.2 The receiving Party shall:
Protect Confidential Information with at least the same degree of care it uses for its own.
Not disclose such information to any third party without prior written consent.
4.3 These obligations survive termination for ten (10) years, or perpetually for trade secrets.

5. DATA PROTECTION AND SECURITY
5.1 Client acknowledges that Services may involve processing of personal data.
5.2 Company makes no warranty that its systems are immune from cyberattack, intrusion, or data breach.
5.3 Client assumes all regulatory risk associated with data processed under this Agreement, including fines, penalties, and notification obligations.
5.4 Client shall indemnify Company against any claims arising from data provided by Client.

6. WARRANTIES DISCLAIMER
6.1 SERVICES ARE PROVIDED “AS IS” AND “AS AVAILABLE.”
6.2 COMPANY DISCLAIMS ALL WARRANTIES, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING:
MERCHANTABILITY
FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE
NON-INFRINGEMENT
UNINTERRUPTED OR ERROR-FREE OPERATION
6.3 Company does not guarantee regulatory compliance of deliverables.

7. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY
7.1 To the maximum extent permitted by law, Company’s total aggregate liability shall not exceed the total fees paid by Client in the thirty (30) days preceding the claim.
7.2 Under no circumstances shall Company be liable for:
Indirect damages
Consequential damages
Lost profits
Business interruption
Loss of data
7.3 These limitations apply even if a remedy fails of its essential purpose.

8. INDEMNIFICATION (HIGH-RISK ALLOCATION)
8.1 Client shall defend, indemnify, and hold harmless Company and its affiliates, officers, directors, employees, and agents from and against any and all claims, including third-party claims, regulatory penalties, and governmental investigations arising from:
Client’s use of the Services
Client’s data
Client’s violation of law
Any integration with third-party systems
8.2 This indemnification obligation is uncapped and survives termination.

9. LIQUIDATED DAMAGES
9.1 If Client breaches Sections 3 (IP), 4 (Confidentiality), or 8 (Indemnification), Client agrees to pay liquidated damages of $250,000 per breach, acknowledging that actual damages would be difficult to calculate.
9.2 Liquidated damages are cumulative and not exclusive of other remedies.

10. TERMINATION
10.1 Company may terminate this Agreement immediately for convenience upon written notice.
10.2 Client may terminate only upon:
90 days’ written notice; and
Payment of all remaining fees due under any active SOW.
10.3 Upon termination:
All licenses immediately cease.
Client shall delete all Company proprietary materials.
Outstanding payment obligations accelerate and become immediately due.

11. NON-COMPETE AND NON-SOLICITATION
11.1 During the term and for two (2) years thereafter, Client shall not develop, market, or support any product substantially similar to Company’s offerings.
11.2 Client shall not solicit or hire Company employees during the term and for 24 months thereafter.

12. DISPUTE RESOLUTION
12.1 Any dispute shall be resolved exclusively by binding arbitration under the rules of [Arbitration Body].
12.2 Arbitration shall occur in [Jurisdiction].
12.3 Each Party waives:
Jury trial rights
Class action participation
Consolidated proceedings
12.4 The prevailing Party shall recover attorneys’ fees and costs.

13. FORCE MAJEURE
Company shall not be liable for delays or failures caused by events beyond its reasonable control, including but not limited to acts of God, war, terrorism, pandemics, labor disputes, government actions, or infrastructure failure.
